seal     : A protein that has folded the wrong way, and that — touching its normal twins — teaches them to misfold too, until the corruption spreads like an infection and kills. No DNA, no RNA, no genome of any kind: a prion copies itself by shape alone. Inheritance, and contagion, carried in the fold of a single molecule.
